name: benet-labs-electro-mechanics-amp-controls-laboratory
notes: The Electro-Mechanics and Controls (EM&amp;C) Laboratory is a multi-faceted facility focused on armament related electro-mechanical components and assemblies with capabilities that include engineering design, fabrication and testing using state of the art tools.   The EM&amp;C Laboratory provides customer support through an environment enabling the Benet workforce to integrate electronic/electrical hardware with computer-based control systems. Hardware activities performed typically focus on armament test equipment &amp; test support items, encompassing multi-axis actuation control, power management &amp; sensor interfacing. Computer-based rapid prototyping of control systems thru use of The MathWorks control development tool suite. Modern electronic test equipment is applied consisting of digitizing oscilloscopes, waveform generators, logic analyzers, digital multimeters, current probes, and PC-based data acquisition.   Our Virtual.Lab software expertise gives us the capability to simulate and optimize the performance of electro-mechanical systems for structural integrity, system dynamics and Matlab control feedback. In Virtual.Lab, we build accurate simulation models, simulate their real-life performance, assess electro-mechanical control designs and optimize end-to-end performance before prototype construction.
title: Benet Labs Electro-Mechanics & Controls Laboratory
